1
00:00:05,746 --> 00:00:07,432
Take everything in moderation.

2
00:00:08,281 --> 00:00:09,574
This is my reward for you.

3
00:00:09,887 --> 00:00:10,815
-Here.
-Alright.

4
00:00:10,899 --> 00:00:12,256
If so,

5
00:00:12,340 --> 00:00:13,257
I'll take the entire pot.

6
00:00:13,341 --> 00:00:14,480
I don't want to share it with you.

7
00:00:19,401 --> 00:00:20,277
Just pour a little for me.

8
00:00:20,360 --> 00:00:21,438
-Come on.
-Take everything in moderation.

9
00:00:21,521 --> 00:00:22,561
You said so yourself.

10
00:00:24,321 --> 00:00:25,158
-Just a little more.
-Stop drinking.

11
00:00:25,241 --> 00:00:26,663
-Just a little more.
-Stop drinking. Have some food.

12
00:00:26,746 --> 00:00:27,597
Alright.

13
00:00:27,680 --> 00:00:28,798
Your mouth is so oily.

14
00:00:28,881 --> 00:00:29,961
Wipe your mouth.

15
00:00:30,160 --> 00:00:31,480
Stop drinking.

16
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:35,078
Wait. What are you doing?

17
00:00:35,161 --> 00:00:36,161
Hey.

18
00:00:36,281 --> 00:00:37,281
There's not much left.

19
00:00:37,801 --> 00:00:39,001
-Just a little.
-Just a little?

20
00:00:39,080 --> 00:00:40,285
-Yeah.
-Just a little, okay?

21
00:00:40,721 --> 00:00:41,998
Only a little.

22
00:00:42,081 --> 00:00:44,101
That's enough.
That's too much.

23
00:00:46,240 --> 00:00:47,441
Cheers.

24
00:00:47,801 --> 00:00:49,038
You don't understand, right?

25
00:00:49,520 --> 00:00:51,518
Cheers is what they say in English.

26
00:00:52,441 --> 00:00:53,441
Cheers.

27
00:00:58,400 --> 00:00:59,680
How much did you drink?

28
00:01:00,001 --> 00:01:01,281
How did you get so drunk?

29
00:01:02,120 --> 00:01:04,001
I'll make some hangover soup for you.

30
00:01:42,880 --> 00:01:43,880
Here.

31
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:45,680
Drink this.

32
00:01:51,960 --> 00:01:53,960
Don't you know how much liquor

33
00:01:54,801 --> 00:01:55,801
you can drink?

34
00:01:56,680 --> 00:01:58,600
I'm teaching students in accordance

35
00:01:59,361 --> 00:02:00,680
with their aptitude.

36
00:02:02,161 --> 00:02:05,320
First, I lure her in with desire.

37
00:02:05,960 --> 00:02:09,081
After that, I'll bring her to
the righteous path.

38
00:02:12,801 --> 00:02:14,600
Tou Tou is a promising child.

39
00:02:15,801 --> 00:02:16,918
It's just that it's difficult

40
00:02:17,001 --> 00:02:18,760
to be her teacher.

41
00:02:19,361 --> 00:02:20,361
Look at me.

42
00:02:21,001 --> 00:02:22,361
I'm giving everything I got

43
00:02:23,001 --> 00:02:25,001
to realise Master's dream.

44
00:02:25,441 --> 00:02:26,998
I've never seen you put this much effort

45
00:02:27,081 --> 00:02:28,161
in teaching Tian Zhen.

46
00:02:28,320 --> 00:02:29,079
It's because I know

47
00:02:29,162 --> 00:02:30,918
Tian Zhen

48
00:02:31,001 --> 00:02:32,400
belongs here.

49
00:02:35,320 --> 00:02:36,721
He can't run away.

50
00:02:40,161 --> 00:02:41,321
But Tou Tou?

51
00:02:42,240 --> 00:02:43,518
She might run away

52
00:02:43,601 --> 00:02:44,800
if we take our eyes off her.

53
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:46,278
I think

54
00:02:46,361 --> 00:02:48,360
you're sure that I won't run away.

55
00:02:48,601 --> 00:02:50,001
That's why you make
endless demands of me.

56
00:02:51,441 --> 00:02:53,120
Dear, that sounds unfair to me.

57
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:55,240
Unfair?

58
00:02:55,721 --> 00:02:57,001
Was I wrong?

59
00:02:59,441 --> 00:03:00,520
You put so much effort

60
00:03:01,881 --> 00:03:03,117
in treating outsiders.

61
00:03:03,200 --> 00:03:04,360
What about your family?

62
00:03:07,721 --> 00:03:08,721
This is

63
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:10,960
a common problem among humans.

64
00:03:11,601 --> 00:03:12,601
We always show outsiders

65
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:14,960
our best side

66
00:03:15,360 --> 00:03:17,920
and show our family members
our worst side.

67
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:24,837
Don't think

68
00:03:24,920 --> 00:03:26,717
that I invited Tou Tou to drink with me

69
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:28,601
so that I could transform her.

70
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:31,640
I was cleaning up the mess
your son had made.

71
00:03:32,321 --> 00:03:33,360
If so, why didn't you let him

72
00:03:33,601 --> 00:03:35,001
treat the girl during the forum?

73
00:03:37,721 --> 00:03:39,321
So, you were waiting
to say that all along?

74
00:03:41,441 --> 00:03:42,597
I was wondering

75
00:03:42,680 --> 00:03:43,918
why everything

76
00:03:44,001 --> 00:03:45,161
wasn't proceeding smoothly lately.

77
00:03:45,561 --> 00:03:47,161
Your son wasn't ready yet.

78
00:03:48,001 --> 00:03:49,520
If you don't let him give it a try,

79
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:51,881
he'll never be ready.

80
00:03:53,001 --> 00:03:54,001
Both you

81
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:55,960
and Uncle were around.

82
00:03:58,001 --> 00:04:00,358
And, he wanted to send Tian Zhen
to give the girl a diagnosis.

83
00:04:00,441 --> 00:04:02,721
He wanted to see how capable
Tian Zhen was.

84
00:04:03,001 --> 00:04:05,561
You only look on the bright side.

85
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:07,721
What if your son

86
00:04:08,360 --> 00:04:10,080
made things worse?

87
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:11,800
If Tou Tou made things worse,

88
00:04:12,080 --> 00:04:14,360
everyone could at least
come to terms with it.

89
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:15,881
I could back her up.

90
00:04:16,881 --> 00:04:17,881
But if I send your son there

91
00:04:18,360 --> 00:04:19,360
and back him up,

92
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:21,597
the Song family

93
00:04:21,680 --> 00:04:22,960
will be embarrassed.

94
00:04:24,721 --> 00:04:26,360
I didn't send your son there

95
00:04:26,721 --> 00:04:29,001
in order to protect him.

96
00:04:29,841 --> 00:04:30,841
Goodness.

97
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:33,649
This concerns the girl's life, you know?

98
00:04:34,080 --> 00:04:35,400
Listen.

99
00:04:36,161 --> 00:04:38,360
I'll tell you this.

100
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:41,721
Although Tou Tou is boorish,

101
00:04:42,041 --> 00:04:43,400
she's talented.

102
00:04:43,881 --> 00:04:45,358
She's talented

103
00:04:45,441 --> 00:04:47,441
and she's meant to take this path.

104
00:04:48,120 --> 00:04:49,638
She might be distracted

105
00:04:49,721 --> 00:04:51,680
during our lessons,

106
00:04:53,001 --> 00:04:54,918
however, she has a delicate heart.

107
00:04:55,001 --> 00:04:57,041
Her eyes and ears were open
and receptive.

108
00:04:58,441 --> 00:04:59,478
She remembered everything

109
00:04:59,561 --> 00:05:01,321
I said and taught.

110
00:05:01,561 --> 00:05:02,960
Not only did she observe what I taught,

111
00:05:04,001 --> 00:05:05,001
but she could also apply them.

112
00:05:05,561 --> 00:05:06,678
She observed that Mr Zheng's daughter

113
00:05:06,761 --> 00:05:08,561
had eczema.

114
00:05:09,120 --> 00:05:10,120
When your son was there,

115
00:05:10,561 --> 00:05:11,561
he only said

116
00:05:11,841 --> 00:05:12,841
that she had a fever.

117
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:15,037
He may be able to cure her fever,

118
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:16,680
but he'll never think of

119
00:05:16,881 --> 00:05:18,678
making egg yolk oil on the scene

120
00:05:18,761 --> 00:05:19,761
and letting the girl apply it.

121
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:21,800
Do you think he'll think of that?

122
00:05:22,161 --> 00:05:23,441
He'll never think of that.

123
00:05:24,281 --> 00:05:25,798
The people there might have

124
00:05:25,881 --> 00:05:27,717
a doctorate or a Master's degree,

125
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:28,639
but none of them

126
00:05:28,722 --> 00:05:30,800
can do any better than Tou Tou.

127
00:05:32,841 --> 00:05:33,759
You're excited and proud

128
00:05:33,842 --> 00:05:35,240
when you talk about Sun Tou Tou.

129
00:05:38,321 --> 00:05:39,321
You feel like throwing up again?

130
00:05:41,841 --> 00:05:42,841
I'll go to the toilet.

131
00:05:52,960 --> 00:05:54,120
Li Quan applied for leave again?

132
00:05:54,281 --> 00:05:56,317
Yes, this is already the second time
this month.

133
00:05:56,400 --> 00:05:57,157
And, he applied for leave once

134
00:05:57,240 --> 00:05:58,240
during our weekend lesson.

135
00:05:59,841 --> 00:06:00,841
Tian Zhen,

136
00:06:01,721 --> 00:06:03,001
did you know that Li Quan
applied for leave?

137
00:06:03,561 --> 00:06:04,561
I know that.

138
00:06:05,881 --> 00:06:06,881
Where did he go?

139
00:06:07,281 --> 00:06:08,281
He...

140
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:09,800
He's doing a part-time job.

141
00:06:10,841 --> 00:06:11,841
A part-time job?

142
00:06:14,400 --> 00:06:15,400
What does that mean?

143
00:06:17,120 --> 00:06:17,974
He's doing foot massages.

144
00:06:18,057 --> 00:06:19,037
Dr Song,

145
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:20,317
someone left their belongings
in the storeroom.

146
00:06:20,400 --> 00:06:21,400
Come and take a look.

147
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:30,800
Call Zhao Li Quan.

148
00:06:31,441 --> 00:06:32,441
Tell him to pack his belongings.

149
00:06:33,441 --> 00:06:34,881
How could he keep them here?

150
00:06:36,841 --> 00:06:38,120
This is a medical centre, not a hotel.

151
00:06:39,680 --> 00:06:41,601
The medicine we use
will be consumed by the patients.

152
00:06:43,960 --> 00:06:46,037
Where will he stay then?

153
00:06:46,120 --> 00:06:46,918
Take his things out.

154
00:06:47,001 --> 00:06:48,001
How is that my business?

155
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:52,120
Tian Zhen,

156
00:06:52,441 --> 00:06:54,321
is Li Quan facing any difficulties?

157
00:06:55,321 --> 00:06:57,960
I lent him my dorm last time.

158
00:06:58,161 --> 00:06:59,437
But the dorm had tight security.

159
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:01,357
I told him to stay here
for the time being.

160
00:07:01,440 --> 00:07:03,078
I think he's going to rent a unit soon.

161
00:07:03,161 --> 00:07:03,918
That's why he applied for leave

162
00:07:04,001 --> 00:07:05,841
in order to work outside.

163
00:07:06,560 --> 00:07:07,797
He should find a job

164
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:09,960
with stable income.

165
00:07:10,721 --> 00:07:12,000
He can come and learn

166
00:07:12,161 --> 00:07:13,161
when he has time.

167
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:16,241
If so, you can just give him a job.

168
00:07:16,960 --> 00:07:18,440
Just make him a pharmaceutical worker.

169
00:07:18,681 --> 00:07:20,121
He can prepare prescriptions.

170
00:07:20,520 --> 00:07:21,718
He can study at the same time.

171
00:07:21,801 --> 00:07:22,758
And, he'll make some money too.

172
00:07:22,841 --> 00:07:23,841
Isn't that the best of both worlds?

173
00:07:25,601 --> 00:07:28,041
Zhao Li Quan will be
a doctor in the future.

174
00:07:29,520 --> 00:07:32,357
He can't just steal other people's jobs.

175
00:07:32,440 --> 00:07:33,440
Go and ask him.

176
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:35,560
It's either he continues his study

177
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,000
or works outside.

178
00:07:37,801 --> 00:07:39,560
You're discriminating against him here.

179
00:07:40,161 --> 00:07:42,117
Why can Peng Shi Yan work
while studying then?

180
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:43,361
Why can't Zhao Li Quan do the same?

181
00:07:44,440 --> 00:07:46,198
Peng Shi Yan

182
00:07:46,281 --> 00:07:48,681
doesn't make a living
as a TCM practitioner.

183
00:07:49,121 --> 00:07:51,281
TCM is Zhao Li Quan's livelihood.

184
00:07:51,560 --> 00:07:52,598
He needs medical skills

185
00:07:52,681 --> 00:07:54,560
to make a living, understood?

186
00:07:56,080 --> 00:07:57,481
I think Tian Zhen's suggestion

187
00:07:58,681 --> 00:08:00,117
is worth considering.

188
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:01,801
It might work.

189
00:08:02,481 --> 00:08:03,601
If Li Quan is around,

190
00:08:04,241 --> 00:08:05,237
at least he can help us out

191
00:08:05,320 --> 00:08:07,721
when we're busy preparing prescriptions.

192
00:08:08,241 --> 00:08:09,681
He's familiar with herbs and medicine.

193
00:08:10,121 --> 00:08:11,440
And, he was professionally trained
in this field.

194
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:14,477
He can prepare prescriptions

195
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:15,640
when we give diagnoses.

196
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,520
He can study with the other classmates

197
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:18,760
when there's a class.

198
00:08:18,880 --> 00:08:20,440
This is our place after all.

199
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:23,237
We can pay him according to
a part-timer's rate.

200
00:08:23,320 --> 00:08:24,320
What do you think?

201
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:26,477
Niece-in-law already said so much.

202
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:27,318
Nephew,

203
00:08:27,401 --> 00:08:29,200
why don't you consider it?

204
00:08:31,241 --> 00:08:32,760
Why are you calling me Nephew again?

205
00:08:33,640 --> 00:08:36,440
Because it's time for me
to show my authority as your senior.

206
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:46,281
I know you guys are
doing this for his sake.

207
00:08:47,121 --> 00:08:49,278
But the thing is,

208
00:08:49,361 --> 00:08:50,400
Zhao Li Quan

209
00:08:50,560 --> 00:08:52,917
must understand what he truly desires.

210
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,440
That's the main thing.

211
00:08:54,657 --> 00:08:55,657
That's it for now.

212
00:08:57,481 --> 00:08:58,481
Call him.

213
00:08:59,241 --> 00:09:00,241
He can't stay here.

214
00:09:06,640 --> 00:09:07,357
So, does that mean

215
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:08,440
your father has agreed to it?

216
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:11,361
Your seniority does work wonders.

217
00:09:23,801 --> 00:09:24,639
You've been applying for leave

218
00:09:24,722 --> 00:09:25,880
just to work here?

219
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:29,200
Quit the job.

220
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:31,317
You're a postgraduate student
from a decent medical academy.

221
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:33,560
Why are you working
in a massage parlour?

222
00:09:33,921 --> 00:09:35,117
I'll get you a decent job.

223
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:36,200
-Come with me.
-Tian Zhen.

224
00:09:39,640 --> 00:09:40,640
Thank you.

225
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:42,718
You always helped me out.

226
00:09:42,801 --> 00:09:44,000
I feel pretty bad about it.

227
00:09:44,560 --> 00:09:45,357
I appreciate your kindness,

228
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:46,237
but I'm doing great here.

229
00:09:46,320 --> 00:09:47,320
Doing great?

230
00:09:47,520 --> 00:09:48,238
You apply for leave during the day.

231
00:09:48,321 --> 00:09:49,640
You don't even attend
our lessons on the weekend.

232
00:09:49,921 --> 00:09:51,801
My father was unhappy that
you applied for leave today.

233
00:09:52,121 --> 00:09:52,918
Besides, if you work at night,

234
00:09:53,001 --> 00:09:54,841
you won't have the energy to
attend class on the second day.

235
00:09:55,121 --> 00:09:56,598
If there's a situation in your family,

236
00:09:56,681 --> 00:09:57,557
-you can tell me.
-Tian Zhen.

237
00:09:57,640 --> 00:09:58,640
I can help you out.

238
00:10:02,640 --> 00:10:04,320
I know you're doing it for my sake.

239
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:07,921
But it's not like I can accept your help

240
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:11,241
every time without any pressure.

241
00:10:14,760 --> 00:10:16,241
I'm a man too. I have my dignity.

242
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:17,638
You said this yourself.

243
00:10:17,721 --> 00:10:19,237
You said you would find a mentor
in the apprentice class

244
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:20,557
and ask them to take you
under their wing.

245
00:10:20,640 --> 00:10:21,718
How could you learn from them

246
00:10:21,801 --> 00:10:22,801
when you're doing this?

247
00:10:24,640 --> 00:10:25,718
I do want to get a mentor

248
00:10:25,801 --> 00:10:27,000
and learn under them.

249
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:30,320
However, I need to survive first.

250
00:10:31,361 --> 00:10:32,361
You saw this yourself.

251
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:34,361
I've always been working outside.

252
00:10:35,440 --> 00:10:36,477
It was different when I was in college.

253
00:10:36,560 --> 00:10:37,398
Back then, I was just
providing for myself.

254
00:10:37,481 --> 00:10:38,398
I didn't need to provide for my family.

255
00:10:38,481 --> 00:10:39,199
Now, it's different.

256
00:10:39,282 --> 00:10:40,880
Now, I have to make money
and provide for my family.

257
00:10:42,921 --> 00:10:44,198
Forget it. Let's drop the topic.

258
00:10:44,281 --> 00:10:45,281
You won't understand anyway.

259
00:10:46,481 --> 00:10:48,357
Your starting point is the endpoint
I've been trying to achieve.

260
00:10:48,440 --> 00:10:49,598
Wait. What did you say?

261
00:10:49,681 --> 00:10:51,121
-Wait.
-This is...

262
00:10:51,241 --> 00:10:53,241
What are you guys saying?

263
00:10:54,361 --> 00:10:55,598
You guys are going off-topic here.

264
00:10:55,681 --> 00:10:56,960
It's way off-topic.

265
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:00,880
Is it that complicated?

266
00:11:01,241 --> 00:11:02,520
Do you wish to find

267
00:11:02,880 --> 00:11:04,038
a way for you to study

268
00:11:04,121 --> 00:11:05,681
and make money at the same time?

269
00:11:05,921 --> 00:11:07,241
Right now, there's such a deal.

270
00:11:07,841 --> 00:11:09,440
It can satisfy your need to study

271
00:11:09,560 --> 00:11:11,158
and help you make money too.
Do you want it or not?

272
00:11:11,241 --> 00:11:12,241
Why are you here?

273
00:11:12,361 --> 00:11:13,560
Why the heck are you here?

274
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:15,078
Didn't you come here

275
00:11:15,161 --> 00:11:16,477
to help your friend?

276
00:11:16,560 --> 00:11:18,398
You already arranged
something for him, right?

277
00:11:18,481 --> 00:11:20,198
Just tell him.

278
00:11:20,281 --> 00:11:21,237
Tell him everything.

279
00:11:21,320 --> 00:11:22,079
Tell him both the pros and cons.

280
00:11:22,162 --> 00:11:23,797
Let him make the call.

281
00:11:23,880 --> 00:11:25,718
He's the one making the call here,
not you.

282
00:11:25,801 --> 00:11:28,080
Why are you acting like
you're his father?

283
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:29,917
But you!

284
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:30,917
You kept interrupting him

285
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:31,878
when he was trying

286
00:11:31,961 --> 00:11:33,320
to tell you about it.

287
00:11:33,481 --> 00:11:34,997
I was so fed up.

288
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:37,477
Can't you just wait for him
to finish his words

289
00:11:37,560 --> 00:11:38,921
before you interrupt?

290
00:11:43,241 --> 00:11:44,241
Just cut to the chase.

291
00:11:44,801 --> 00:11:45,880
Don't talk about anything else.

292
00:11:47,880 --> 00:11:49,281
You can work as a pharmaceutical worker
in my family's medical centre.

293
00:11:49,801 --> 00:11:51,161
You can attend class when there's one.

294
00:11:51,760 --> 00:11:52,760
My father has already agreed to it.

295
00:11:57,440 --> 00:11:58,440
Thank you.

296
00:11:59,121 --> 00:12:00,121
Thank you.

297
00:12:01,880 --> 00:12:02,880
Don't mention it.

298
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:04,320
Yeah.

299
00:12:04,681 --> 00:12:05,801
Here you go.

300
00:12:06,560 --> 00:12:07,640
Isn't it simple?

301
00:12:07,880 --> 00:12:09,078
You guys would've argued

302
00:12:09,161 --> 00:12:11,721
for three hours if I weren't here.

303
00:12:12,320 --> 00:12:13,320
Quan,

304
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:15,244
you might not be able to
live in the medical centre anymore.

305
00:12:15,408 --> 00:12:16,158
That's fine.

306
00:12:16,241 --> 00:12:17,838
I'll get my wage soon.

307
00:12:17,921 --> 00:12:19,481
I'll stay in a cheap place
for the time being.

308
00:12:23,880 --> 00:12:24,880
Okay.

309
00:12:30,801 --> 00:12:31,801
Fools.

310
00:13:25,121 --> 00:13:26,121
Xing Xing.

311
00:13:26,880 --> 00:13:27,880
We meet again.

312
00:13:28,681 --> 00:13:29,477
Dear,

313
00:13:29,560 --> 00:13:30,560
you're here to pick me up?

314
00:13:32,361 --> 00:13:33,361
Someone's following me.

315
00:13:42,080 --> 00:13:43,080
Is he gone?

316
00:13:47,681 --> 00:13:48,681
He should be gone.

317
00:13:52,640 --> 00:13:53,640
That was terrifying.

318
00:13:54,121 --> 00:13:56,038
That guy followed me
all the way here from the subway.

319
00:13:56,121 --> 00:13:57,320
He kept staring at me.

320
00:13:57,681 --> 00:13:58,917
Listen. Next time, if you encounter
someone like him,

321
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:00,200
just stare at him.

322
00:14:00,801 --> 00:14:02,041
People like him are timid.

323
00:14:02,440 --> 00:14:03,358
I'm not Tou Tou.

324
00:14:03,441 --> 00:14:04,921
I dare not stare at him.

325
00:14:10,320 --> 00:14:11,320
What are you doing here?

326
00:14:14,320 --> 00:14:15,320
I...

327
00:14:16,801 --> 00:14:17,801
You must make sure
your centre of gravity

328
00:14:18,080 --> 00:14:19,921
is between your legs.

329
00:14:20,560 --> 00:14:21,560
Wait.

330
00:14:21,923 --> 00:14:23,361
Wait.

331
00:14:24,320 --> 00:14:25,320
Who's calling you?

332
00:14:27,320 --> 00:14:28,320
It's Xing Xing.

333
00:14:33,121 --> 00:14:34,121
Hello?

334
00:14:34,801 --> 00:14:36,801
Sun Tou Tou, what have you done?

335
00:14:37,440 --> 00:14:39,041
What do you mean
by sending a guy to my house?

336
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:40,918
Xing Xing,

337
00:14:41,001 --> 00:14:43,000
it's pretty late now.

338
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:45,237
Have you taken dinner?

339
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:47,281
Did you work overtime again?

340
00:14:47,681 --> 00:14:49,078
I'm sure it's tough on you.

341
00:14:49,161 --> 00:14:50,560
I'm heartbroken.

342
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:52,080
Don't interrupt me.

343
00:14:52,321 --> 00:14:53,237
Tell me.

344
00:14:53,320 --> 00:14:54,477
You sent a man to my house.

345
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:55,518
What should I do?

346
00:14:55,601 --> 00:14:56,997
(Xing Xing, listen.)

347
00:14:57,080 --> 00:15:00,237
Quan is so pitiful.

348
00:15:00,320 --> 00:15:01,917
Not only can he not afford food,

349
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:03,917
but he also
can't afford a place to stay.

350
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,917
(My bed is vacant anyway.)

351
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:07,198
(That's why I sent him there.)

352
00:15:07,281 --> 00:15:08,718
(Can you take pity on him)

353
00:15:08,801 --> 00:15:09,838
and take him in?

354
00:15:09,921 --> 00:15:10,839
I promise.

355
00:15:10,922 --> 00:15:12,317
He's a good guy.

356
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:14,681
He won't cross the line.

357
00:15:14,921 --> 00:15:16,158
I don't know if he's a good guy or not,

358
00:15:16,241 --> 00:15:18,361
but he's a guy.

359
00:15:18,880 --> 00:15:20,400
(That's even better.)

360
00:15:20,640 --> 00:15:23,080
I thought it was dangerous for you
to live alone.

361
00:15:23,320 --> 00:15:24,640
Now, there's a guy to protect you.

362
00:15:24,724 --> 00:15:26,164
I can rest at ease now.

363
00:15:31,800 --> 00:15:33,280
(And, Xing Xing, think about it.)

364
00:15:33,481 --> 00:15:34,399
(He knows how to give massages.)

365
00:15:34,482 --> 00:15:35,798
If you have issues like a stiff neck,

366
00:15:35,881 --> 00:15:37,680
you don't even need to
go to the massage parlour.

367
00:15:37,881 --> 00:15:38,759
Just stay at home.

368
00:15:38,842 --> 00:15:41,318
First come, first served, right?

369
00:15:41,401 --> 00:15:43,241
(Isn't it convenient?)

370
00:15:43,800 --> 00:15:45,121
You'll land me in trouble eventually.

371
00:15:57,761 --> 00:15:58,761
What? You expect me
to carry your luggage?

372
00:16:11,881 --> 00:16:12,881
Slowly.

373
00:16:13,001 --> 00:16:13,798
You must be careful when you go up.

374
00:16:13,881 --> 00:16:15,121
-Come on.
-Let's continue.

375
00:16:15,721 --> 00:16:16,721
Maintain your centre of gravity.

376
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:19,200
Okay.

377
00:16:21,440 --> 00:16:22,761
Feel the harmony between man and nature.

378
00:16:32,121 --> 00:16:33,121
Say,

379
00:16:33,680 --> 00:16:34,798
is chiropractic

380
00:16:34,881 --> 00:16:35,679
the thing

381
00:16:35,762 --> 00:16:37,680
where they pop the bones?

382
00:16:38,361 --> 00:16:39,361
That's not it.

383
00:16:39,841 --> 00:16:41,280
Ms Dong doesn't do that.

384
00:16:41,560 --> 00:16:42,997
It's dangerous when
you crack bones like that.

385
00:16:43,080 --> 00:16:44,438
No, that's not what I mean.

386
00:16:44,521 --> 00:16:45,398
I mean popping the bones.

387
00:16:45,481 --> 00:16:46,358
There's a sound to it.

388
00:16:46,441 --> 00:16:48,278
What's the difference between them?

389
00:16:48,361 --> 00:16:49,678
Cracking

390
00:16:49,761 --> 00:16:50,639
makes a different sound.

391
00:16:50,722 --> 00:16:51,758
Popping makes a different sound.

392
00:16:51,841 --> 00:16:52,758
That's the difference.

393
00:16:52,841 --> 00:16:53,877
It's the same thing.

394
00:16:53,960 --> 00:16:55,401
How could they be the same?

395
00:16:56,001 --> 00:16:57,237
The difference is

396
00:16:57,320 --> 00:16:58,997
that chiropractic is fake.

397
00:16:59,080 --> 00:17:00,601
It's a lie.

398
00:17:01,361 --> 00:17:02,440
It's already good enough

399
00:17:02,641 --> 00:17:05,121
for massages and the likes
to help our bodies to relax.

400
00:17:05,241 --> 00:17:06,601
We mustn't abuse

401
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:08,680
the power of rumours.

402
00:17:09,001 --> 00:17:10,521
It'll harm the people.

403
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:11,638
That's why I think

404
00:17:11,721 --> 00:17:13,038
TCM practitioners
can focus on healthcare

405
00:17:13,121 --> 00:17:14,521
while doctors can focus on treatments.

406
00:17:14,680 --> 00:17:15,478
We should stay on our designated trails.

407
00:17:15,561 --> 00:17:16,721
Isn't that better?

408
00:17:17,241 --> 00:17:18,197
I don't know about the others,

409
00:17:18,280 --> 00:17:19,877
but Ms Dong is a living deity.

410
00:17:19,960 --> 00:17:21,121
If she does work her magic,

411
00:17:21,320 --> 00:17:23,200
you'll feel like you've been reborn.

412
00:17:23,721 --> 00:17:25,197
I know her for many years.

413
00:17:25,280 --> 00:17:26,118
I saw for myself

414
00:17:26,201 --> 00:17:27,278
that patients in wheelchairs

415
00:17:27,361 --> 00:17:29,001
could walk out of the room
after her treatment.

416
00:17:29,241 --> 00:17:30,320
Guys, listen to him.

417
00:17:30,680 --> 00:17:32,398
She used her hand
to restore the position of the bones,

418
00:17:32,481 --> 00:17:34,960
and that could achieve
the effect of surgeries.

419
00:17:35,440 --> 00:17:36,641
Don't you think it's ridiculous?

420
00:17:36,881 --> 00:17:38,237
Even doctors can't guarantee

421
00:17:38,320 --> 00:17:40,160
that a cripple could walk out of
the room after surgery.

422
00:17:41,481 --> 00:17:42,318
Pick it up.

423
00:17:42,401 --> 00:17:44,001
Look. He's resorting to this
when he can't win the argument.

424
00:17:59,841 --> 00:18:01,038
You deserved it.

425
00:18:01,121 --> 00:18:02,197
Shi Yan, you'd better believe it.

426
00:18:02,280 --> 00:18:04,237
There's an old lady called Luo You Ming
in Shuangqiao, Beijing.

427
00:18:04,320 --> 00:18:05,638
She could set bones

428
00:18:05,721 --> 00:18:06,721
with just her hands.

429
00:18:06,960 --> 00:18:09,200
Premier Zhou even
built a hospital for her.

430
00:18:09,401 --> 00:18:10,319
She could

431
00:18:10,402 --> 00:18:13,429
set fractures, even crushed bones

432
00:18:13,512 --> 00:18:14,512
and restore them.

433
00:18:14,920 --> 00:18:16,117
Is that Ms Dong

434
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:18,158
as good as the old lady
in Shuangqiao, Beijing?

435
00:18:18,241 --> 00:18:20,121
If that's the case, she's even better
than my nephew then.

436
00:18:20,721 --> 00:18:21,721
Yeah.

437
00:18:21,960 --> 00:18:23,001
Is Mr Ren here?

438
00:18:28,521 --> 00:18:29,638
This must be the classroom.

439
00:18:29,721 --> 00:18:30,761
That's Zhu's car.

440
00:18:31,721 --> 00:18:32,721
He's here?

441
00:18:35,841 --> 00:18:37,320
Mr Ren!

442
00:18:38,721 --> 00:18:40,190
I finally found you!

443
00:18:40,273 --> 00:18:41,273
Mr Zhu,

444
00:18:41,361 --> 00:18:43,881
I thought we had an appointment
in the medical centre on Monday?

445
00:18:44,479 --> 00:18:46,396
I couldn't sleep well
for the past few days.

446
00:18:46,480 --> 00:18:48,514
(Zhu Chang Ming) I was
flustered. I couldn't wait any longer.

447
00:18:48,641 --> 00:18:50,241
Mr Ren, please read my pulse.

448
00:18:51,226 --> 00:18:52,226
(Dong Hui Ci)
Check my pulse.

449
00:18:52,320 --> 00:18:53,400
Yeah.

450
00:18:53,481 --> 00:18:56,518
I just received a batch of
top-quality cordyceps.

451
00:18:56,601 --> 00:18:58,241
There are only 1,000 of them in one jin.

452
00:18:58,521 --> 00:18:59,521
I bought 500,000 yuan
worth of cordyceps.

453
00:18:59,721 --> 00:19:00,960
Should I consume it?

454
00:19:01,121 --> 00:19:02,798
Or should I

455
00:19:02,881 --> 00:19:04,398
consume the 60-years-old
wild ginseng I have?

456
00:19:04,481 --> 00:19:05,481
What do you think?

457
00:19:05,939 --> 00:19:06,939
What about this?

458
00:19:07,121 --> 00:19:08,638
You can tell us

459
00:19:08,721 --> 00:19:10,038
the "tonics"

460
00:19:10,121 --> 00:19:12,278
you think that are good for you

461
00:19:12,361 --> 00:19:13,721
lately.

462
00:19:13,881 --> 00:19:14,881
I took plenty of them.

463
00:19:15,839 --> 00:19:17,639
Turtles,
ginseng,

464
00:19:17,722 --> 00:19:18,717
dendrobium, sea cucumbers,

465
00:19:18,800 --> 00:19:19,639
I took everything.

466
00:19:19,722 --> 00:19:21,881
So, do you feel better
after taking them?

467
00:19:22,241 --> 00:19:24,080
Or do you feel uncomfortable?

468
00:19:24,721 --> 00:19:25,758
It's like this.

469
00:19:25,841 --> 00:19:27,558
I think it's only worth it

470
00:19:27,641 --> 00:19:29,117
if I take such expensive tonics.

471
00:19:29,200 --> 00:19:30,798
I make a lot of money.

472
00:19:30,881 --> 00:19:31,881
What else should I spend them on
besides food?

473
00:19:32,641 --> 00:19:33,881
So, you have too much money, huh?

474
00:19:34,401 --> 00:19:35,721
You should do charity with them then.

475
00:19:36,200 --> 00:19:38,121
You can donate to our apprentice class.

476
00:19:38,841 --> 00:19:40,320
Mr Ren, it's like this.

477
00:19:40,481 --> 00:19:42,318
I can't donate my money when I'm alive.

478
00:19:42,401 --> 00:19:43,198
I'll donate everything to you

479
00:19:43,281 --> 00:19:44,798
once I'm dead.

480
00:19:44,881 --> 00:19:46,158
Donating my money

481
00:19:46,241 --> 00:19:47,721
is just like donating my organs.

482
00:19:48,001 --> 00:19:49,241
I'll feel terrible.

483
00:19:50,320 --> 00:19:51,678
Zhu, you need to understand this.

484
00:19:51,761 --> 00:19:52,841
Herbs and tonics are used

485
00:19:53,320 --> 00:19:55,241
to rectify a deviation.

486
00:19:56,121 --> 00:19:58,158
Not all tonics can be consumed.

487
00:19:58,241 --> 00:20:00,038
Judging from your current condition,

488
00:20:00,121 --> 00:20:01,320
it's useless

489
00:20:01,521 --> 00:20:02,521
to take any kind of tonics.

490
00:20:02,721 --> 00:20:04,158
Even so, I have to take something.

491
00:20:04,241 --> 00:20:06,237
Give me a prescription.
Give me a prescription.

492
00:20:06,320 --> 00:20:07,320
You?

493
00:20:07,601 --> 00:20:08,641
Listen.

494
00:20:09,320 --> 00:20:11,398
Carrot and Chinese cabbages
are your best bet.

495
00:20:11,481 --> 00:20:12,877
Seasonal and cheap ingredients

496
00:20:12,960 --> 00:20:14,398
are best for you.

497
00:20:14,481 --> 00:20:15,601
Just adjust your diet.

498
00:20:16,121 --> 00:20:17,721
Take your meal on time
and sleep on time.

499
00:20:18,361 --> 00:20:19,518
I can't sleep.

500
00:20:19,601 --> 00:20:22,241
I wouldn't need to be here
if I could sleep in the first place.

501
00:20:22,601 --> 00:20:23,601
What do you think?

502
00:20:25,761 --> 00:20:27,080
Did you owe people money lately?

503
00:20:27,386 --> 00:20:28,386
No.

504
00:20:28,521 --> 00:20:29,521
Did someone owe you money?

505
00:20:30,601 --> 00:20:31,601
Are you afraid that
you can't get it back?

506
00:20:36,147 --> 00:20:37,238
I can't treat that.

507
00:20:37,321 --> 00:20:38,278
Don't say that.

508
00:20:38,361 --> 00:20:40,278
Mr Ren, you have to
do something about me.

509
00:20:40,361 --> 00:20:41,361
You have to think of something.

510
00:20:44,241 --> 00:20:46,001
You can't just ignore me.

511
00:20:46,121 --> 00:20:46,918
What should I do then?

512
00:20:47,001 --> 00:20:48,001
Give me a prescription.

513
00:20:49,200 --> 00:20:50,200
Have you done some movements

514
00:20:51,001 --> 00:20:53,121
that rotate your spine?

515
00:20:54,320 --> 00:20:55,841
What do you mean?

516
00:20:56,361 --> 00:20:57,481
He plays golf.

517
00:20:59,361 --> 00:21:01,200
Did you play golf for the past few days?

518
00:21:01,841 --> 00:21:03,678
I play golf twice per week.

519
00:21:03,761 --> 00:21:04,918
I stopped playing golf after last week

520
00:21:05,001 --> 00:21:05,997
as I couldn't sleep.

521
00:21:06,080 --> 00:21:07,080
I didn't play golf this week.

522
00:21:07,881 --> 00:21:08,877
Do you know something?

523
00:21:08,960 --> 00:21:10,481
When you play golf,

524
00:21:10,721 --> 00:21:12,157
you're rotating your spine

525
00:21:12,241 --> 00:21:13,721
with this movement.

526
00:21:14,241 --> 00:21:15,159
This movement

527
00:21:15,242 --> 00:21:17,837
caused your thoracic vertebra
to shift to the wrong position.

528
00:21:17,920 --> 00:21:20,001
And that has affected the function
of your lungs and heart.

529
00:21:20,121 --> 00:21:22,080
That's why you couldn't sleep.

530
00:21:22,241 --> 00:21:23,960
I'll restore them

531
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:25,200
to their original positions later.

532
00:21:25,641 --> 00:21:27,121
You'll be able to sleep well tonight
after that.

533
00:21:35,721 --> 00:21:37,440
You should give me a prescription.

534
00:21:38,761 --> 00:21:40,680
If Ms Dong said she could treat you,

535
00:21:41,080 --> 00:21:42,881
she could definitely treat you.

536
00:21:47,241 --> 00:21:48,361
Are you sure?

537
00:21:50,601 --> 00:21:51,601
Guys,

538
00:21:52,481 --> 00:21:54,477
for our chiropractic class,

539
00:21:54,560 --> 00:21:56,398
I've invited Ms Dong Hui Ci,

540
00:21:56,481 --> 00:21:58,001
whom I respect a lot.

541
00:21:58,320 --> 00:21:59,721
She bumped into

542
00:22:00,001 --> 00:22:01,278
a patient at the entrance.

543
00:22:01,361 --> 00:22:03,361
She's treating him right now.

544
00:22:03,601 --> 00:22:04,678
That's why

545
00:22:04,761 --> 00:22:06,040
I'm doing the introduction.

546
00:22:07,881 --> 00:22:09,560
Ms Dong is here. Let's welcome her.

547
00:22:12,241 --> 00:22:13,241
Ms Dong,

548
00:22:13,361 --> 00:22:14,438
how's the patient?

549
00:22:14,521 --> 00:22:15,518
He's asleep.

550
00:22:15,601 --> 00:22:17,560
Professor Song is looking after him.

551
00:22:18,601 --> 00:22:19,601
Guys,

552
00:22:19,881 --> 00:22:20,881
for today's class,

553
00:22:21,320 --> 00:22:23,841
it'll definitely be interesting and fun.

554
00:22:24,080 --> 00:22:25,601
We'll show you guys

555
00:22:27,001 --> 00:22:28,638
that not only can chiropractic
treat illness,

556
00:22:28,721 --> 00:22:30,560
but it can also treat major illnesses.

